DAY 2 | Azure cloud challenge [2/30]:
Step 0: Log in to the Azure Portal (https://portal.azure.com/).

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

1. Create a VM and attach multiple NIC with it:

---> Steps to create a Virtual machine is given below:

Step 1: Navigate to Virtual Machines in menu bar [Located in top left corner of home] (or) you can search Virtual machines in Search bar.
Step 2: Select Azure Virtual Machine.
Step 3: Enter the following details:
      -> Resource Group: you can create a new one or select the existing one.   [ your choice ]
      -> Virtual Machine name
      -> Region
      -> Image
      -> Size
      -> In administrator account : enter Username, password and Confirm Password.
Step 4: Move on to Disk and select Standard SSD.
Step 5: Leave Others as it is.
Step 6: Click on "REVIEW + CREATE".
Step 7: once reviewed, click on "CREATE" to create the Virtual Machine.
Step 8: Once deployment is complete, you can click on go to resource to view the Virtual Machine.

---> Steps to attach multiple NIC - Network Interface Card:

Step 1: In your VM go to Network Settings in menu bar and click on "ATTACH NETWORK INTERFACE".
Step 2: Enter the following details:
      -> NIC name
      -> IP Configuration
      -> Vnet
Step 3: Click "ADD" to create the Network Interface Card [NIC].
Step 4: Once delpoyement is done, go to the resource to check the NIC.


___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________



2.  Create Private and Public Subnets in the Virtual Network:

---> steps to create a private and public subnets:
Step 1: In home page, open the already created Virtual Machine.
Step 2: Go to the "SUBNETS" in the menu bar located in your Virtual Network.
Step 3: Click on the "ADD" to create either a Public or Private Subnet.
Step 4: When adding public subnet click on no to add Private access.
Step 5: When adding private subnet click on yes to add Private access.


